<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-31T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-31T19:00:00-05:00" n="264" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">852.48/1458: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Consul General at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-31T20:00:00-04:00">March 31,
                                1943—8 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>602. For Murphy. Lisbon’s 34, March 27 to you. Have any vessels left or are
                        they leaving in the near future to pick up French refugees in Portugal? Is
                        there any reason why Portuguese request that the vessels call at Vila Real
                        rather than at Lisbon cannot be granted?</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>